  "prompt": "How do you say \"little sister\" in tagalog?",
  "response": "The most common and widely used word for \"little sister\" in Tagalog is **\"nakababatang kapatid na babae\"**.\n\nHowever, you can also use these variations:\n\n*   **\"Bunso\"** - While technically meaning \"youngest child,\" it's often used affectionately to refer to a little sister, especially if she is the youngest in the family.\n*   **\"Ading\"** - This is an Ilocano word, also meaning younger sibling, that Filipinos sometimes use especially when someone is known to have Ilocano roots.\n\nSo, the best options are:\n\n*   **Formal/General:** Nakababatang kapatid na babae\n*   **Informal/Affectionate (if she's the youngest):** Bunso",
